<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1602&amp;p=14287#p14287"><![CDATA[
1. Once a scanline should be enough, since that's approximately how often the Zapper updates the read signal.<br />2. Light colors will also trigger it, but for a shorter period of time (normally, if you aim the zapper at a solid white screen, it will register a hit for about 25 scanlines or so).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Sun Jun 18, 2006 5:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
