<author><name><![CDATA[Memblers]]></name></author>
<updated>2006-06-02T13:09:52-07:00</updated>
<published>2006-06-02T13:09:52-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1602&amp;p=13755#p13755</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1602&amp;p=13755#p13755"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Light Zapper]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1602&amp;p=13755#p13755"><![CDATA[
I have a zapper demo here:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/zappa.zip" class="postlink">http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/zappa.zip</a><br /><br />It's really simple though, it doesn't check the trigger and it displays an all-white screen.  It changes the pitch of the sound depending on where on the screen it's pointed.<br /><br />To read the zapper, you have to poll it constantly.  Like every scanline (114 cpu cycles or so), reading it only during vblank like a controller won't work.  The good part of that is that you can narrow down the target by counting the scanlines, but the bad part is that it keeps the CPU busy for most of the frame.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Jun 02, 2006 1:09 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
